        <h3 class="article__heading">01. Challenge</h3>

        <p>When the MBTA in Boston came to Thoughtbot, they had an objective that they wanted to solve: <strong>How might we improve communication between officials on the Green Line?</strong></p>

        <p>Being that a problem of this nature could be solved in a myriad of different ways, we decided to use Design Thinking to tackle the problem with its solution-based, user-centric approach. The five phases of the Design Thinking process are: Empathize, Define, Ideate, Prototype, Test. With a small team of six designers and developers, we set out to do these phases over the course of three months, with the goal of having software in the hands of Green Line officials quickly to get feedback and continue iteration from there.</p>

