        <h2 class="article__subheader">Define</h2>
        <p>After a day‚Äôs interviews were over, we would come together as a team and synthesize. We captured our observations (things we heard, saw, felt) on sticky notes, and over time clustered similar ones together to form overarching insights. We came up with 30+ insights, all of which could easily spin off into their own product offering. The task at hand was prioritizing these insights and choosing one that we could tackle together in this short time that would yield the highest impact. This marked the second phase of the Design Thinking process: Define. Now it was up to us to use these insights to determine an objective to work towards that focuses on a critical, common unmet need that we heard throughout our interviews.</p>

        <div class="article__image-container">
          <div>
