        <p>Once we had a better understanding of all the different players and the nature of their relationships (the questions they asked each other and the blockers they experienced), we revisited our insights and determined that <strong>reducing radio chatter</strong> would have the greatest impact on their community. At this time there was one radio channel that handled all the communication on the Green Line, and there were times it was taken up with questions that could be easily answered through software (eg. who is operating a particular train). Questions like these prevented more urgent information from being distributed, which ultimately caused a breakdown in communication.</p>

